---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const trail = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Contact', href: '/contact' },
];
---

<Base
  title="Contact"
  description="Get in touch with Colin Shove via email, or follow the writing on the colinshove.com blog."
  breadcrumbs={trail}
>
  <article class="measure">
    <h1>Contact</h1>

    <p>
      The simplest way to reach me is by email:
      <a href="mailto:hello@colinshove.com">hello@colinshove.com</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For Frively work (websites for local businesses, the Visibility Spec, Pulse
      assessments), the better front door is the
      <a href="https://frively.com">Frively site</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>If you write</h2>

    <p>
      A short message is plenty. Tell me what brought you here and what you are
      hoping to do next. I read everything and reply to anything that needs a
      reply.
    </p>

    <h2>Follow the writing</h2>

    <p>
      The <a href="/blog">writing index</a> has everything, and the
      <a href="/rss.xml">RSS feed</a> updates whenever I publish something new.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
